   geographic distances. Penstemon albidus and P. whippleanus flowers
   increase in size from south-north, while P. glandulosus and P. speciosus
   exhibited an east-west increasing trend. Additionally, mean annual
   precipitation was the most important variable influencing P. glandulosus
   flower morphology. Conclusions: Geographic distance facilitates
   isolation-by-distance and isolation-by-phenology as well as abiotic
   differences between populations; however, other factors such as
   pollinators might be keeping populations morphologically homogeneous
   despite large geographic distance.},
